                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1460">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 816.48/2</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Minister
                            <persName type="to">Long</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-06-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 9, 1917</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your undated telegram received to-day. You will, at your earliest opportunity
                    express to President Melendez the deep distress felt in the United States and by
                    this Government at the calamity which has befallen a. sister Republic. In
                    conveying the heartfelt sympathy of the United States you will make such offer
                    of assistance as may seem desirable in the circumstances.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
